The paper deals with the Maximum-Weighted Independent Set problem on intersection graphs of paths on a grid, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper also uses techniques from approximation algorithms and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper involves graph theory and approximation algorithms, which are covered by cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
